:SHORT_TEXT_START

Border conflict between Libya and Chad 
--------------------------------------
After the fall of Gaddafi's regime the new Libyan government is struggling to maintain its popularity among the Libyan people and therefore decides in a gamble to launch a military operation in order to occupy the contested of the Aouzou strip which has been claimed by the Libyans as being their territory and gain popular support even despite the International Court of Justice ruled in 1994 that the Aouzou Strip belongs to Chad. Sudan which is claimed to be supporting Libya is suspected to have sent Su-25 attack aircraft and helicopters to southern Libya.
Opposing the Libyan military offensive and defending the Aouzou Strip is the combined military forces of Chad and Cameroon. With this the old conflict over the contested territory of Aouzou strip reemerges.  
*
mission by Ricnunes


